# Release Log – WCAG Summary (CRITICAL)

When producing a **release log**, **changelog**, or **release notes**, you **must**:

## 1. Include WCAG Summary

Add a **WCAG Accessibility** section that summarizes the current state from `docs/WCAG-ANALYSIS.md`:

- Target conformance level (WCAG 2.1 Level AA)
- Count of criteria: Met / Partial / Needs verification / N/A
- Brief status (e.g. "Most criteria met; 3 need verification, 2 partial")

## 2. Highlight Actionable Entries

**Actionable** = items that require follow-up. Call them out explicitly:

| Type | Examples |
|------|----------|
| **Needs verification** | Contrast, document title, `lang` attribute |
| **Partial** | Skip link missing, ng-select label association |
| **Known violations** | color-contrast (timescale label), ng-select in panel |
| **Recommendations** | High/Medium priority items from §8 |

Format actionable items as a **bulleted list** with clear next steps, e.g.:

- **High:** Add skip link ("Skip to main content")
- **High:** Fix ng-select label association for panel
- **Medium:** Fix timescale label contrast (4.42 vs 4.5:1)
- **Medium:** Verify document `<title>` and `<html lang>`

## 3. Reference Source

Link or cite `docs/WCAG-ANALYSIS.md` so readers can see full details.
